        <div1 type="summary">
            <p><add hand="#barker">Austin confirms a militia election.</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p><persName>Stephen F. Austin lieutenant Colonel of the Militia of the
<placeName>Colony on the Colorado and Brazos rivers in the Province of Texas</placeName></persName>
and charged by the <persName>Mexican Govt </persName>with the appointment of the
<persName>Militia officers</persName> of said Colony untill its organization is completed&#8212;<pb n="807"/></p>

<p>It appearing by the official returns of the election held on the
<date when="1824-05-15">15 day of May instant</date> for the <persName>officers of the <placeName>upper detachment of
the Colorado</placeName></persName> that <persName>Jessee Burnam</persName> was duly elected <persName>Captain of said
detachment</persName>, therefore I do by these presents appoint the said <persName>Jessee
Burnam Captain</persName> of said <placeName>upper detachment of the Colorado</placeName> to hold
said commission untill the organization of the <persName>Battalion </persName>may render
a new election necesary or until the <persName>Govt. of this <placeName>Province</placeName></persName> orders
otherwise&#8212;hereby commanding the <persName>Militia </persName>of said <persName>detachment </persName>to
obey their said <persName>captain </persName>accordingly</p>

<p>Given at the Town of <placeName>San Felipe de Austin</placeName> in the <placeName>Province of
Texas</placeName> this<date when="1824-05-28"> 28 of may 1824, 4, 3</date></p>

<p><persName>S. F. A</persName></p>

        </div1>
